  "text": "The FD value of a one-dimensional physiological signal is calculated as the change in length of recursively defined self-similar curves with the measurement scale. The length of curve used in computation was the same as described in the study of Arjunan and Kumar [CITATION_1] . By plotting the logarithm of the average length of curve versus the logarithm of the time interval, the FD is obtained as the slope of the fitted linear line.",
